Ok, hosts don't work, you have to block the access using a Firewall like ESET, once you block any attempt to phone home, it will work, except Premier Pro, PPro doesn't start unless you give it an access to internet, it just hangs in there at splash screen, but when you let it through it barks the serial, something has to be done about it.

@iluvwarez

thanks for the update, however it doesn't solve the problem. Premier Pro, After Effects and Encore don't start unless they are given the access to the internet, they all stop initialization with a splash screen that says "Loading ExporterQuickTimeHost.prm", this solution makes video editing impossible. I think the actual files need to be patched so they don't have to phone home. At least this is how it was done with CS4 MC from Mazuki.

Also some more info (not related to above proble, but helps in general): 

After its done installing(Do not run any app yet), head over to:

C: > Program Files (or x86) > Common Files > Adobe > OOBE > PDApp > UWA >

Rename or Add a word at the end of these:

Adobe Application Manager (Updater)

AAM Updates Notifier

updaterstartuputility

I should specify, the programs eventually start, but it may take over 10 minutes. It appears as if it's something Quick Time related, however it starts easily if you let it access the internet, minus key invalidation.

Using Trial from Adobe plus this keymaker with host blocked and ESET firewall.

If you are reading this and know the solution, please share for all.
